WEBVTT

00:00:01.330 --> 00:00:08.330
Over 100 years ago, on October 31, 1916,

00:00:08.330 --> 00:00:12.330
Brother Charles Taze Russell was traveling on a train

00:00:12.330 --> 00:00:15.330
as part of a lecture tour across the United States,

00:00:15.330 --> 00:00:21.329
quite unexpectedly and at the young age of 64,

00:00:21.329 --> 00:00:23.329
Brother Russell died.

00:00:23.329 --> 00:00:27.329
For years, he had been traveling continually.

00:00:27.329 --> 00:00:29.329
You know, it's been said

00:00:29.329 --> 00:00:34.329
that Brother Russell covered more than a million miles.

00:00:34.329 --> 00:00:37.329
Now, of course, some of you may have accomplished that feat,

00:00:37.329 --> 00:00:40.329
but at that time, of course, we're not talking about air travel.

00:00:40.329 --> 00:00:44.329
Brother Russell had to accomplish that by train and ship

00:00:44.329 --> 00:00:47.329
and goodness knows what other means, quite an accomplishment.

00:00:47.329 --> 00:00:53.329
In addition to that, he had delivered more than 30,000 sermons,

00:00:53.329 --> 00:00:55.329
lectures and talks.

00:00:55.329 --> 00:00:58.329
He had written books and other material,

00:00:58.329 --> 00:01:02.329
totaling over 50,000 pages.

00:01:02.329 --> 00:01:05.329
Yet, despite all of the privileges that he had enjoyed,

00:01:05.329 --> 00:01:09.329
his tremendous Bible knowledge and the powerful way

00:01:09.329 --> 00:01:15.329
that Jehovah had used him in just a moment he was gone.

00:01:15.329 --> 00:01:19.329
It really illustrates the truth of what James says here

00:01:19.329 --> 00:01:22.329
in James chapter 4, verses 13 and 14.

00:01:22.329 --> 00:01:25.329
Let's read this together.

00:01:25.329 --> 00:01:28.329
James 4, verse 13.

00:01:28.329 --> 00:01:31.329
Says, come now, you who say today or tomorrow

00:01:31.329 --> 00:01:34.329
will travel to this city and will spend a year there

00:01:34.329 --> 00:01:38.329
and we will do business and make some profit.

00:01:38.329 --> 00:01:42.329
Whereas you do not know what your life will be like tomorrow.

00:01:42.329 --> 00:01:46.329
For you are a mist that appears for a little while

00:01:46.329 --> 00:01:49.329
and then disappears.

00:01:49.329 --> 00:01:50.329
Well, that's true.

00:01:50.329 --> 00:01:53.329
You see, really no matter what privileges we may enjoy,

00:01:53.329 --> 00:01:58.329
how skilled a teacher we may be, what knowledge we've accumulated,

00:01:58.329 --> 00:02:04.329
we're all just like a mist appearing for a while and then disappearing.

00:02:04.329 --> 00:02:09.330
Well, this is an idea that occurs over and over again in the scriptures

00:02:09.330 --> 00:02:13.330
and really with the purpose of encouraging all of us

00:02:13.330 --> 00:02:17.330
to take a close and sober and serious look

00:02:17.330 --> 00:02:20.330
at the way that we use our lives.

00:02:20.330 --> 00:02:25.330
And even more importantly, how we use them to serve Jehovah.

00:02:25.330 --> 00:02:29.330
In Luke chapter 12, you'll remember that Jesus taught

00:02:29.330 --> 00:02:31.330
an illustration regarding a rich man.

00:02:31.330 --> 00:02:32.330
Do you remember this?

00:02:32.330 --> 00:02:34.330
Let's open our Bibles and read it together.

00:02:34.330 --> 00:02:38.669
Luke chapter 12 and verse 16.

